"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-athletics-2024-0825-1466588-repeat-of-olympic-400m-final-as-adeleke-finishes-fourth\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"It was a repeat of the women's 400m Olympic final asRhasidat Adelekefaded in the second half of her Diamond League meet in Silesia, Poland to finish fourth.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 156, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 100, \"end\": 114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"score\": 0.9999999999918145, \"rank\": 8.168892346303913e-12, \"text\": \"Diamond League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\"}, {\"begin\": 123, \"end\": 130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Silesia\", \"score\": 0.6413454529683851, \"rank\": 0.5574844378954582, \"text\": \"Silesia\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Silesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Silesia\"}, {\"begin\": 132, \"end\": 138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.999963861947868, \"rank\": 3.613663567503569e-05, \"text\": \"Poland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just over a fortnight on from her exploits in thewomen's 4x400m relay, and17 days after being edged out of a podium position in the individual 400m final, the 21-year-old was back in action as her 2024 season draws to a close.\", \"from\": 158, \"to\": 384, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With seven of the eight finalists from the Olympic final competing in Poland - only Great Britain's Amber Anning was missing - it was a high quality field, with the Tallaght sprinter stationed in lane seven.\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 593, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 456, \"end\": 462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.999963861947868, \"rank\": 3.613663567503569e-05, \"text\": \"Poland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 470, \"end\": 483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9991565779548539, \"rank\": 0.000775943130308768, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 551, \"end\": 559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tallaght\", \"score\": 0.9999987383210965, \"rank\": 1.2065069801080318e-06, \"text\": \"Tallaght\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tallaght\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tallaght\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adeleke was quick out of the blocks, with her customary strong first 200m once again to the fore as she eased past Lieke Klaver and Sada Williams on her outside.\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 710, \"end\": 722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lieke_Klaver\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lieke Klaver\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lieke_Klaver\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lieke_Klaver\"}, {\"begin\": 727, \"end\": 740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sada_Williams\", \"score\": 0.9999998975108663, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sada Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sada_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sada_Williams\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hitting the bend however, she was reeled in by the big-hitters from Paris, with Dominican Marileidy Paulino again asserting her dominance in the event with a blistering final 100m to repeat her winning exploits in Paris in time of 48.66.\", \"from\": 758, \"to\": 995, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 826, \"end\": 831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998040039, \"rank\": 1.9607092784006741e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 838, \"end\": 847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominican_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9999997934915186, \"rank\": 1.646927348422711e-07, \"text\": \"Dominican\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominican_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominican_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 848, \"end\": 865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marileidy_Paulino\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marileidy Paulino\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marileidy_Paulino\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marileidy_Paulino\"}, {\"begin\": 972, \"end\": 977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998040039, \"rank\": 1.9607092784006741e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bahrain's Salwa Eid Naser and Poland's European champion Natalia Kaczmarek, who has now got the better of Adeleke in all six races they have competed in - again took second and third respectively.\", \"from\": 997, \"to\": 1193, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain\", \"score\": 0.9252471206457591, \"rank\": 0.04598587434527502, \"text\": \"Bahrain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain\"}, {\"begin\": 1007, \"end\": 1022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salwa_Eid_Naser\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Salwa Eid Naser\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salwa_Eid_Naser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salwa_Eid_Naser\"}, {\"begin\": 1027, \"end\": 1033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.999963861947868, \"rank\": 3.613663567503569e-05, \"text\": \"Poland\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Poland_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1036, \"end\": 1053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.606131755676832e-15, \"text\": \"European champion\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/European_Athletics_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 1062, \"end\": 1071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_A._P._Kaczmarek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kaczmarek\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_A._P._Kaczmarek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_A._P._Kaczmarek\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adeleke struggled coming down the stretch to maintain her pace and had to settle for fourth, crossing the line just outside her Olympic time in 50 seconds flat, holding off the surge of Alexis Holmes in fifth.\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1388, \"end\": 1394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"score\": 0.9977115779774731, \"rank\": 0.0022936705815925795, \"text\": \"Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Naser's second-place finish comes on the back of another controversial period for the sprinter, with World Athletics announcing last week that Bahrain Athletics Association (BAA) had conducted itself \\\"negligently and/or recklessly\\\" in relation to anti-doping matters.\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1406, \"end\": 1411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naser_al-Din_Shah_Qajar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5552768658938276e-16, \"text\": \"Naser\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naser_al-Din_Shah_Qajar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naser_al-Din_Shah_Qajar\"}, {\"begin\": 1507, \"end\": 1522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_World_Championships_in_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9900360122034726, \"rank\": 0.010064268040401579, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_World_Championships_in_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2017_World_Championships_in_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 1549, \"end\": 1556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain\", \"score\": 0.9252471206457591, \"rank\": 0.04598587434527502, \"text\": \"Bahrain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Athletics Integrity Unit imposed several penalties, banning Bahrain from all World Athletics Series events for 12 months, starting in June this year, but allowing them to bring a maximum of 10 athletes to the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1681, \"end\": 1705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Integrity_Unit\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Athletics Integrity Unit\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Integrity_Unit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athletics_Integrity_Unit\"}, {\"begin\": 1741, \"end\": 1748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain\", \"score\": 0.9252471206457591, \"rank\": 0.04598587434527502, \"text\": \"Bahrain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Naser is permitted to compete in the Diamond League series as it is not part of the world series.\", \"from\": 1907, \"to\": 2004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1907, \"end\": 1912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naser_al-Din_Shah_Qajar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5552768658938276e-16, \"text\": \"Naser\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naser_al-Din_Shah_Qajar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naser_al-Din_Shah_Qajar\"}, {\"begin\": 1944, \"end\": 1958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"score\": 0.9999999999918145, \"rank\": 8.168892346303913e-12, \"text\": \"Diamond League\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diamond_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Naser served a two-year ban in 2021 for anti-doping whereabouts violations, but was part of the Bahraini Olympic team of 10, winning silver in the 400m final in a season's best time of 48.53.\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2197, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2006, \"end\": 2011, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naser_al-Din_Shah_Qajar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5552768658938276e-16, \"text\": \"Naser\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naser_al-Din_Shah_Qajar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Naser_al-Din_Shah_Qajar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nick Griggsfinished 12th in a 3000m final where Jakob Ingebrigsten stormed to victory and lowered his own world record by more than three seconds with a winning time of 7:17.55.\", \"from\": 2199, \"to\": 2376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2199, \"end\": 2203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Jonas\", \"score\": 0.788437626746436, \"rank\": 0.26832928505988624, \"text\": \"Nick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Jonas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nick_Jonas\"}, {\"begin\": 2247, \"end\": 2252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.13064136296089e-19, \"text\": \"Jakob\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 19-year-old posted a time of 7:39.52, three seconds outside his season's best.\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2460, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sarah Healyposted the second-quickest time of her career in finishing fifth in the women's 1500m final.\", \"from\": 2464, \"to\": 2567, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Having failed to do so in Paris, Healy dipped under four minutes and was just edged out of fourth by Great Britain's Melissa Courtney-Bryant.\", \"from\": 2569, \"to\": 2710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2595, \"end\": 2600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998040039, \"rank\": 1.9607092784006741e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2670, \"end\": 2683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9991565779548539, \"rank\": 0.000775943130308768, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resour